Background
You are part of a select few of a specialist trained counter terrorist ghost unit. Your task, neutralize any ghosts that inhabit your country by any means necessary.

You've received reports of paranormal activity around a rural corn farm concerning a small group gentlemen supposedly trapped there by a small group of ghosts. Get there, and rescue the hostages and destroy any ghosts if necessary.


Video - short demo




Recommended server settings
I highly recommend having a non solid player if possible mod as well as disabling weapon spawners. Flashlights and night-vision goggles are also recommended to be disabled, the lighting in this map is designed very carefully so that the 2 are not necessary, but still manage to keep the ghosts fairly well hidden. Normal gravity is also highly advised, otherwise players will be able to escape outside the map.


Other notes
A nav mesh is included, but it is the one created by default, there are a fair few errors with it with regards to players getting stuck in the basement and such, but hostages tend to cope a lot better.

For the best games with this map (if playing with bots, alone), I recommend a balance of 2 CT's to 1 Ghost on normal difficulty with the player being on Terrorist (or ghost in this case) team. That's just my advise though, it worked out quite nicely for me. Otherwise, 4 v 4 with humans works very nicely too.

Any constructive comments and feedback are appreciated, as always.

This is a new version with alot of bug fixes and general improvements on how the map looked and played.
Some things I fixed/added included: soundscapes, fixed custom sounds, fixed door and stair errors, fixed place names, improved the 3d skybox, added flares to signify hostage rescue areas, packed custom content, and other minor stuff.

I modeled this map very closely after the Gerudo Valley Fortress found in The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time. The layout of the fortress is very similar, I only had to change one or two small things as the dimensions didn't quite match up.

The Counter-terrorists start half near the gate, the others by the stairs. The terrorist start outside, at the top of the fortress. It may seem a bit unbalanced between teams. However after testing with people and bots, it was actually pretty even most of the time.

There are four hostages, the difference is they are spread out unlike most Hostage Rescue maps. The hostages are located the same place as the hostage in Ocarina of Time, to keep with the accuracy of the map.
The map also includes a custom nav file and Radar Overlay.


Easter Eggs!

There is a lever on one of the walls outside. When puled, you will hear the Sounds of Storms. and the fairy fountain will open up.

The radio, near the fruit crates outside, can change music, just press use on the front of it to the Koroki Shop music. All radios that play music, will stop if they take damage.

If you redistribute this map elsewhere, make sure you keep the credits there, You do not need to have this whole Readme, but everyone should be credited for their role in this map.

Here's the final version of my map, originally called "cs_atlas". I'm calling it 'final' because I'm trying to move on to other projects...

The map was made with lower-end computers in mind, so some of the geometry and prop placement is a bit sparse, and there is no HDR support.

There are a total of 40 spawnpoints in the map, to help support servers with higher player counts. However, it seems to play best with around 16 players. 

I also included a version of the map with no buyzones or hostages, suitable for GG or CSDM. 

Enjoy!


**EDIT** 
I had to fix an issue with some of the physics objects in the map. I've renamed the updated map "cs_gentech_final".

Forest Insurrection - Hostage Rescue 

Counter-Terrorists: An Elite Rescue Team has been air lifted to an old building at the far end of the valley. Your mission is to rescue the remaining 4 hostages from the terrorist's stronghold and bring them back safely to the 
insertion point.  If the rescue mission is not going well, there is an old cave that you bring the hostages to where they will be safe.

Terrorists: You were already given a large ransom payment for the hostages but decided to ask for more money. Being that you don't like to hear "no", your group killed one of the hostages and will kill more unless the extra money is delivered! 

Funtime is over.  Someone must pay!

========

Mr.Breen was working in his office as usual, but 1 day he saw via his window that _thugs_ who have _kidnapped 4 scientists_ are working on something bad.

_Mr.Breen calls the police_ and informs them about this. The _police sends the CT force_ to rescue the hostages(in this case, the scientists)

The T's order the _scientists to create a certain chemical which makes explosives_.

**_While T's protect them from the police and supply them technology, the CT's arrive in time and get armed to fight the terrorists and resuce the scientists._**

=====================

Birds are chirping on the tree merrily when everything is right.
A pool with 2 restrooms in the middle of the map.
The Tspawn is a farmhouse.
The CTspawn is Mr.Breen's office.
A subway which links the CTspawn, Tspawn and the middle of the map.
A storage room in the subway.

A hostage rescue map inspired by Frank Lloyd Wright's Kaufmann House.
This version is a reduced version of the HL2 map (the guest house is not present, for example)
All the artwork in the house was made by the map author and belongs to him. All the textures are either Valve's work or the author's work. The geometry was also built by the author based on information found freely around the world wide web.

There are 4 hostages in the house. CT forces have the advantage of a quicker trip to the hostages, but terrorists can use the many terraces and exits of the house to take out the CTs. Due to the nature of the building, there are multiple ways to approach and defend the house, making each round different.

The performance is still far from optimal, specially when it comes to long-range battles. Hopefully, this map will be more playable as computers become more powerful, who knows. There are several occluders placed to help performance but they don't help as much as we would like... Use HDR only if your computer can handle it. The LDR lighting looks a bit more yellow while the HDR has a prettier orange light. This could be fixed with another 5 hour compile, so I'm sorry if you don't like how the LDR version looks.

A lot of graphical changes were done to the map. Higher-res pictures, more accurate stone textures, better lighting using smoothing groups, HDR and fixed "most" of the lightmap grid problems. Most of the windows and doors now use 2D textures to help with performance. It might not look as good as the HL2 version in that sense, but good performance was seen as more important. The river now uses a new custom material which is refractive, scrolling and mildly reflective. It looks better than the static HL2 water, fits the situation better and also helps with performance.

Some things are different to ordinary cs maps: The hostages can be at 5 different places and in the controlroom there is a screen which can be used to see the camera covering the storage-entrance. The exitdoor from the changing-rooms is looked and can only be opened from inside.
